<chapter>
<title>Tips and Tricks</title>

<section>
<body>

  <p><b>Multiple X-Sessions</b></p>

  <p>XFree86 allows you to have multiple X sessions open at once. This
    can be useful if you want or need two different desktop
    environments open at once.</p>

  <pre>
    <codenote>By default X uses the display :0</codenote>
% <i>startx</i>
    <codenote>To open a second display, use another number</codenote>
% <i>startx -- :1</i> </pre>

  <p>The desktops will be on terminals F7-F12</p>
</body>
</section>
